			<p>Good job.  You just mocked Brandybuck for holding a libertarian value.  To say that some course of action, like mask wearing or social distancing, is useful in combating the coronavirus, but should not be mandatory, is explicitly libertarian.  I don&#8217;t need to pretend that seatbelts are useless or harmful in order to object to seatbelts, and if I thought masks or social distancing were useless, then my objection to them would be rooted in pragmatism, not libertarianism.  To a libertarian, whether or not they are effective is irrelevant to whether or not they should be mandated.</p>		</div>

